text: A myeon, myŏn, myon, or township is an administrative unit in South Korea; along with town (urban), a township (rural) is a division of a county and some cities of fewer than 500,000 population. Township have smaller populations than towns and represent the rural areas of a county or city. Township are subdivided into villages.
